Patch summary:
Seed the desktop "Pointer speed" slider at its slowest position. AOSP's
SettingsProvider ships def_pointer_speed=0 (the slider's mid-point); set it to
-7 so Settings.System.POINTER_SPEED defaults to the far-left (slowest) end of
the -7..7 range when the settings database is first created. The Cuttlefish
first-boot provisioning script re-asserts the same value. Kept as a standalone
patch so the default can be reverted independently of the OTA-default seeding
in frameworks-base-settingsprovider-ota.patch.

diff --git a/packages/SettingsProvider/res/values/defaults.xml b/packages/SettingsProvider/res/values/defaults.xml
index e3b61c852a8a..f00f6d94d439 100644
--- a/packages/SettingsProvider/res/values/defaults.xml
+++ b/packages/SettingsProvider/res/values/defaults.xml
@@ -132,7 +132,7 @@
     <bool name="def_show_ime_with_hard_keyboard">false</bool>
 
     <!-- Default for Settings.System.POINTER_SPEED -->
-    <integer name="def_pointer_speed">0</integer>
+    <integer name="def_pointer_speed">-7</integer>
 
     <!-- Default for DTMF tones enabled -->
     <bool name="def_dtmf_tones_enabled">true</bool>
